This paper is likely to belong to the Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC) category as it discusses a programming environment specifically targeting cache-coherent shared-memory multi-cores. It may also belong to the Programming Languages (cs.PL) category as it mentions the use of C++ template libraries. Additionally, it could be categorized under the Architecture (cs.AR) and Performance (cs.PF) categories as it discusses the use of lock-free synchronization mechanisms and offloading workloads to unused CPUs. Finally, it may also belong to the Software Engineering (cs.SE) category as it emphasizes the trade-off between human productivity and execution efficiency.
